All Bay Area counties, followed by the state of California, have announced shelter-in-place orders restricting many forms of nonessential activities.
Seniors and people with disabilities may be eligible to receive community meals, and many grocery stores offer senior-only hours.
Six Bay Area counties are now requiring grocery stores to ban reusable bags as a measure to curb the spread of the virus.
Many Bay Area grocery stores have been limiting the number of customers allowed in the store at a single time, though some stores have imposed no such limitations.
A: Yes, many grocery stores offer delivery, but there are delays on popular delivery services like Amazon Fresh and Instacart.